Introduction

Youjoung is a South Korean singer under RND Company and a former member of the girl group BB GIRLS (formerly Brave Girls). She joined Brave Girls on February 2, 2016, as part of a lineup expansion, alongside Minyoung, Eunji, Yuna, and Hayun. She officially debuted with the group on February 16th, with their fourth digital single, "Deepened".

She, alongside Eunji, participated in the idot rebooting project show The Unit in late 2017. However, she was eliminated in episode 11, ranking 37th place. On February 16, 2023, Brave Entertainment announced the conclusion of Brave Girls' activities after the members decided not to renew their contracts.

Shortly after the announcement of the group's disbandment, on April 27, 2023, Warner Music Korea announced that Youjoung and other members signed exclusive contracts to continue as a group under the name BB GIRLS, due to trademark ownership by Brave Entertainment. However, on April 22, 2024, it was revealed that BB GIRLS would continue as a trio without Youjoung after leaving Warner Music Korea.
